{
  "__template_notes": [
    "Replace placeholders: <APP>, <GHCR_OWNER>, <HF_REPO>, <HF_REVISION>, <APP_REQUIRED_KEY>.",
    "The <APP>_* env vars follow a per-project prefix convention. Rename everything to match your app's prefix.",
    "DO NOT add the two anti-cheating integrity flags (your <APP>_OFFLINE_FIXTURES and <APP>_DETERMINISTIC_OVERRIDES equivalents) to env — the contract requires them UNSET in staging/production.",
    "Staging and production specs MUST differ only in workersMin/workersMax/name/env.<APP>_ENVIRONMENT. Everything else identical.",
    "PORT_HEALTH is MANDATORY (env block, same value as PORT for the standard single-port case). RunPod's LB poller uses PORT_HEALTH (NOT PORT) to find /ping. If PORT_HEALTH is missing, the worker boots cleanly, FastAPI serves /ping 204/200, but the gateway never sees it and the endpoint stays `unhealthy` forever with NO ERROR in any log. This is the silent killer — see pitfalls-37.md #25 and setup-guide §6.1.2. The deploy script must refuse any LB spec without PORT_HEALTH.",
    "dockerStartCmd is MANDATORY on every spec — never omit. RunPod IGNORES the Dockerfile's CMD when the base image already declares its own (TEI, TGI, vLLM, NIM, Whisper, faster-whisper, etc. all ship one). Without dockerStartCmd, the base image's binary runs in place of your start.sh, dies with no args in milliseconds, and the worker exits code 1 with an EMPTY Container logs panel — looks identical to a corrupt image. See pitfalls-37.md #26 and setup-guide §6.1.3. The deploy script must refuse any spec without it.",
    "Companion to dockerStartCmd: the Dockerfile MUST set an explicit ENTRYPOINT (NOT `ENTRYPOINT []`). Use `ENTRYPOINT [\"bash\", \"/app/start.sh\"]` and `CMD []`. The empty-array form is supposed to clear the inherited entrypoint per the OCI spec, but RunPod's runtime doesn't honor it reliably — the base image's inherited entrypoint hijacks dockerStartCmd as args, model-server dies in milliseconds, worker exits code 1 with empty Container logs EVEN THOUGH dockerStartCmd is set correctly. See pitfalls-37.md #27 and setup-guide section 6.1.4.",
    "DO NOT hard-code HF_HOME or HUGGINGFACE_HUB_CACHE in env. Let start.sh / boot.py do runtime detection: read from /runpod-volume/huggingface-cache/hub (RunPod's host-cached models, populated by spec.modelName) when present, fall back to /tmp. Hard-coding /tmp here defeats FlashBoot — every scale-from-zero re-downloads the entire model (3-5 min for 7-8 GB). /runpod-volume here is NOT a user-attached Network Volume — it's a host-local cache mount, does NOT pin region. See pitfalls-37.md #30 and setup-guide section 6.1.7.",
    "DO NOT use workersMin: 1 + flashBootType: OFF as a workaround for /ping timeouts. That defeats the entire serverless cost model. The actual cause is one of pitfalls #25-#31. Walk the silent-killers checklist.",
    "DO NOT rely on bash `:=` or Python `setdefault` to set HF cache vars in start.sh / boot.py. TEI/TGI/vLLM/NIM/Whisper bases preset HUGGINGFACE_HUB_CACHE=/data (and similar) in image ENV; conditional assignment becomes a NO-OP and your runtime detection is silently ignored. The hf_cache_resolved log says `runpod-host` but `printenv` inside the container shows `/data`, model loader hangs forever on ENOENT with no error. Use UNCONDITIONAL assignment: `HUGGINGFACE_HUB_CACHE=\"...\"` in bash, `os.environ[\"HUGGINGFACE_HUB_CACHE\"] = \"...\"` in Python. See pitfalls-37.md #31 and setup-guide section 6.1.8.",
    "Spec env-var keys MUST match what the application actually reads. If app.py has `os.getenv(\"QWEN3_RERANKER_MODEL_PATH\", \"/runpod-volume/models/Qwen3-Reranker-8B\")`, setting `\"MODEL_PATH\": \"...\"` in spec env is a SILENT NO-OP. Run the parity audit on every (spec, app) pair. See pitfalls-37.md #32 and setup-guide section 6.1.9.",
    "Background-load pattern in app.py: the `_target` thread MUST set `self._load_error = f\"{type(exc).__name__}: {exc}\"` in its `except Exception:` block. Without it, load failure is silent and /ping returns 204 forever. See pitfalls-37.md #33 and setup-guide section 6.1.10.",
    "Worker Dockerfile MUST set `ENV HF_HUB_ENABLE_HF_TRANSFER=0` (or requirements.txt MUST include `hf_transfer>=0.1.6`). Base images preset =1; without one of the two fixes, every HF download raises immediately. See pitfalls-37.md #34 and setup-guide section 6.1.11.",
    "RIGHT-SIZE `containerDiskInGb` and `gpuIds`. Formula: `containerDiskInGb = model_size_gb + 5 + (5 if vLLM else 0)`, rounded to nearest 5. For `gpuIds`, include the smallest pool that fits VRAM (4B → 24GB, not 48GB+). Over-provisioning shrinks scheduler's eligible host pool by 3-10×. See pitfalls-37.md #35 and setup-guide section 6.1.12.",
    "workersMax MUST be >= 3 even in staging. NEVER set workersMax: 1 — it puts the endpoint in `throttled` state INDEFINITELY because RunPod allocates one (host, GPU) candidate slot and waits for that exact host to free up. Symptom: Worker shows `Throttled`, Logs tab is empty (looks identical to a hung container). With wmax=3, RunPod allocates 3 candidate slots. Cost impact: ZERO — wmax is a cap, not an allocation. See pitfalls-37.md #37 and setup-guide section 6.1.14."
  ],
  "name": "<APP>-staging",
  "endpointType": "LOAD_BALANCER",
  "registryImage": "${DEPLOY_REGISTRY_IMAGE}",
  "publicRegistry": false,
  "registryAuthName": "ghcr-<APP>",
  "registryUsername": "<GHCR_OWNER>",
  "registryPasswordEnv": "GHCR_PAT",
  "templateName": "<APP>-staging-template",
  "containerDiskInGb": 30,
  "ports": [
    "8080/http"
  ],
  "dockerStartCmd": [
    "bash",
    "/app/services/<APP>/start.sh"
  ],
  "gpuIds": "BLACKWELL_96,BLACKWELL_180,HOPPER_141",
  "gpuTypeIds": [
    "NVIDIA B200",
    "NVIDIA RTX PRO 6000 Blackwell Server Edition",
    "NVIDIA RTX PRO 6000 Blackwell Workstation Edition",
    "NVIDIA H200",
    "NVIDIA H200 NVL",
    "NVIDIA H100 NVL"
  ],
  "modelName": "<HF_REPO>",
  "gpuCount": 1,
  "_locations_note": "DO NOT add dataCenterIds / locations / region / etc. Endpoints MUST be GLOBAL — see pitfalls-37.md #23. The deploy script's _reject_region_pinning() will refuse any spec that pins a region.",
  "workersMin": 0,
  "workersMax": 3,
  "idleTimeout": 60,
  "executionTimeoutMs": 330000,
  "scalerType": "QUEUE_DELAY",
  "scalerValue": 4,
  "flashboot": true,
  "allowedCudaVersions": [
    "13.0",
    "12.8"
  ],
  "env": {
    "<APP>_HF_MODEL_REPO": "<HF_REPO>",
    "<APP>_HF_MODEL_REVISION": "<HF_REVISION>",
    "HF_TOKEN": "${HF_TOKEN}",
    "<APP>_WORKSPACE_ROOT": "/tmp/<APP>-workspaces",
    "<APP>_DISABLE_MODEL_FALLBACK": "0",
    "<APP>_USE_AGENT_RUNTIME": "1",
    "<APP>_MODE": "BENCHMARK_SAFE",
    "<APP>_ENVIRONMENT": "staging",
    "PORT": "8080",
    "PORT_HEALTH": "8080",
    "<APP_REQUIRED_KEY>": "${<APP_REQUIRED_KEY>}"
  }
}
